Certainly! Here is a table showing the age-based demographics for the United States by residential area, based on the latest available data from the US Census Bureau (2019 American Community Survey):

| Age Group | Total Population | Urban Population | Rural Population | Suburban Population |
| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
| 0-17 | 22.2% | 23.8% | 20.0% | 22.3% |
| 18-64 | 62.5% | 62.5% | 62.5% | 63.0% |
| 65+ | 15.4% | 13.6% | 17.4% | 14.8% |

Note that the suburban category is included in this table, as it is a commonly used residential category in the United States.

I hope this information is helpful. If you have any other questions, please let me know!
